text: Kolbeinn Höður Gunnarsson (born 11 July 1995) is an Icelandic sprinter. He won several titles at European Team Championships. He won 14 national titles, mainly 100 m and 200 m. With 20.96, he is the national record holder of 200 m. ==References== ==External links== *IAAF Athlete’s profile Category:Icelandic male sprinters Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Icelandic Athletics Championships winners
